<p valign="top">RECVCLR(2) avr-Xinu RECVCLR(2)</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>NAME</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">recvclr &minus; clear incoming
message buffer asynchronously</p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SYNOPSIS</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;"><i>int recvclr()</i></p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>DESCRIPTION</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">A process executes
<i>recvclr</i> to clear its message buffer of any waiting
message in preparation for receiving messages. If a message
is waiting, <i>recvclr</i> returns it to the caller. If no
messages are waiting, <i>recvclr</i> returns OK.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SEE ALSO</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">receive(2), send(2),
preceive(2), psend(2)</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em">XINU V7
February&nbsp;8, 2011 XINU V7</p>
